natural problem: Find all solutions to the equation $\!\sqrt{2-3z} = 9$.  Express your answer as a common fraction.
natural solution: We square both sides to get rid of the square root sign. This gives us $2-3z = 81$.
We squared an equation, so we have to test our solution to make sure it isn't extraneous.
We have \[\sqrt{2 - 3\left(-\frac{79}{3}\right)} =\sqrt{2+79} = 9,\]so our solution is valid.
